Description.LocalizedString: Thick layers of rot and decay make it impossible to distinguish what’s within.
This was more than rotting pages. This was an invitation to a universe of tales.
There was something real within the pages, as if they told a truth of some kind.
The stories were terrifying, but they held answers to mysteries within the horror.
A casualty of Jake Park’s rugged survivalist lifestyle.
A pleasant image, but once a wave hits all the sand people inside will surely die.
A tick bloated on the blood of Jake Park.
A calm spirit can only go so far when you’ve got dinner to protect.
The compass had acted strangely, as if leading Jake into the Fog.
A bucket of deep-fried fingers, straight from the carnival’s deep fryers.
The circus was full of tricks no sane individual could foresee.
An image so fresh and tantalizing that it’s starkly out of place in this realm.
A stone carving that looked on as Élodie explored the streets below.
An all-time classic that’s one of Jeffrey Hawk’s most valued possessions.
A simple comfort from a memory long ago...
An intensely disturbing floatation device that may be more interested in drowning you.
An urban landscape littered with marks and arrows to explore.
An early design of The Huntress’ mask, carved into scratched and chipped wood.
A grim collection of human fingers and animal parts.
Within the larger figure is a young child, clinging to her doll.
A phenomenon of The Entity’s realm, mysterious and pulsing with blood.
Though broken, the musical instrument served as a memento to Élodie following her parent’s disappearance.
He was angry at the world... and a raccoon too.
He saw what could only be described as a treasure.
Much of the thrill came from the hunt itself.
He knew what he wanted, and no amount of talk could change his mind.
It’s true... the best jokes are when someone gets hurt.
Having escaped to nature, he was free from the pressures of society.
He knew there would be challenges. Primal challenges.
To live, something else must die.
He fought, and he didn’t know on which side of the battle he’d end up.
He would live another day, but it wasn't getting easier...
An ancient depiction of a monstrous creature tormenting four victims.
A terrifying creature of Greek myth. One gaze is enough to petrify.
A Chinese pastry that celebrates the moon.
